<sect1 id="LN">
  <title>LN</title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">LN<indexterm>
      <primary>LN</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>LN function</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis><emphasis>n</emphasis><emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="79.50pt" />

      <colspec colwidth="309.30pt" />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry>n</entry>

          <entry>O número real que será avaliado.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry>Return:</entry>

          <entry>LN retorna um valor real único.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>A função  <emphasis role="bold">LN </emphasis> retorna o logaritmo natural do parâmetro. Trata-se do oposto da função EXP<indexterm>
      <primary> EXP Function</primary>
    </indexterm></para>

  <para>Exemplo:</para>

  <programlisting>MyLogPI := LN(3.14159); //1.14473</programlisting>

  <para>Ver também: <link linkend="EXP">EXP</link>, <link linkend="SQRT">SQRT</link>, <link linkend="POWER">POWER</link>, <link linkend="LOG">LOG</link></para>
</sect1>
